A healthy, balanced meal got carbs, proteins, fats, vitamins, minerals, and water. Carbs give you energy, while proteins is essential for growin' and repairin' body tissues. Fats is also a energy source and help absorb them vitamins that dissolve in fat. Vitamins and minerals is necessary for different body functions, like your immune system and strong bones. Water is key for stayin' hydrated and helps with digestion and absorbin' nutrients.

Everything works together to give you the right nutrition.  For instance, vitamin C helps your body take in iron, makin' your blood healthy. Fiber, which you find in carbs, helps digestion and keeps your blood sugar right. Omega-3 fatty acids, a type of fat, work with proteins to build cell membranes. So, a balanced meal is a mix of nutrients that work together to keep your body runnin' right and keep you healthy.
